While I'm walking over
here, what are you

00:33:50.660 --> 00:33:53.215
watching on Netflix right now?

00:33:53.215 --> 00:33:54.090
MELISSA KING: I know.

00:33:54.090 --> 00:33:59.440
Well, now that "Game of
Thrones" is over, which I love,

00:33:59.440 --> 00:34:05.041
I've been watching "Insecure,"
which I love as well.

00:34:05.041 --> 00:34:06.790
I don't know, what's
out there these days.

00:34:06.790 --> 00:34:09.206
I feel like after "Game of
Thrones," there's nothing else.

00:34:11.775 --> 00:34:13.150
AUDIENCE: This is
kind of random.

00:34:13.150 --> 00:34:18.159
What's your go to cooking
utensil or certain pot

00:34:18.159 --> 00:34:19.600
or pan that's out there?

00:34:19.600 --> 00:34:22.069
I know some people are
really into cast iron.

00:34:22.069 --> 00:34:23.860
MELISSA KING: I was
just about to say that.

00:34:23.860 --> 00:34:27.550
I'm all about everyone
should have a cast iron pan.

00:34:27.550 --> 00:34:30.489
It's like $20, or you
can go to a flea market

00:34:30.489 --> 00:34:32.350
and get it for
probably even cheaper.

00:34:32.350 --> 00:34:34.570
They last forever,
and if you're going

00:34:34.570 --> 00:34:39.159
to just make a steak at home,
it conducts heat way better

00:34:39.159 --> 00:34:40.330
than any other pan.

00:34:40.330 --> 00:34:44.170
And so you'll get a really
nice crust on your steak

00:34:44.170 --> 00:34:45.639
if you cook with that.

00:34:45.639 --> 00:34:49.697
But I cook everything in it,
like fried eggs and fried rice

00:34:49.697 --> 00:34:50.530
and stuff like that.

00:34:50.530 --> 00:34:53.469
So yeah, definitely
get a cast iron.

00:34:53.469 --> 00:34:56.290
Microplanes are
pretty handy as well.

00:34:56.290 --> 00:35:03.737
It's like a little grater that
grates ginger and lemon zest

00:35:03.737 --> 00:35:04.570
and stuff like that.

